& [ZeroWindowingBridge] is a project-local inquiry contract
  + [canonical_specification_uuid] is 1f94d1ea-e2e6-4361-8550-3042668a4481
  + [source_snapshot_uuid] is e6c1074d-3d4a-44b3-9672-0c75e4d36397
  + [project_root] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis
  + [active_authority_root] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop
  + [purpose] is compare sharp zero-pair truncation to a simple Fejer-windowed zero-pair approximation for psi(x)
  + [not_purpose] is proof, disproof, independent zero certification, or final smoothed explicit-formula theorem authority

  = must: compute exact finite pi(x), theta(x), and psi(x) rows for requested x
  = must: compare sharp and fejer window modes with visible zero_pair_count
  = must: expose windowed zero-pair sums, estimate_minus_psi, absolute residual, and scaled residuals
  = must: preserve the window formula and per-zero weights when requested
  = must: treat mpmath zetazero as library numerical lookup, not proof authority
  = must: mark output proof_status as finite_zero_window_probe_not_zero_certification
  = must: compare smoothed rows to the earlier explicit-formula error bridge before drawing a conclusion
  - never: claim RH proof, disproof, or zero certification from finite smoothed zero-term traces
  - never: treat lower residual under one window as universal superiority or convergence proof

& [ZeroWindowProbeTool] is the script surface for the bridge
  + [script] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis\tools\scripts\zero_window_probe.py
  + [runtime_function] is rh_math.explicit_formula.zero_window_probe
  + [input] is finite sample points, zero pair counts, window modes, precision metadata, and optional zero-term inclusion
  + [output] is exact pi/theta/psi rows, windowed explicit-formula estimates, residuals, and optional weighted zero-term rows
  + [proof_status] is finite_zero_window_probe_not_zero_certification

